WEBVTT

00:02.263 --> 00:02.828
[Archie]
Previously onRiverdale...

00:02.872 --> 00:04.004
The Farm left me.

00:04.047 --> 00:05.483
The worthy ascended.

00:05.527 --> 00:07.007
Where's my mom and Polly?

00:07.050 --> 00:08.225
Gone. Everyone is.

00:09.183 --> 00:11.489
I'm Charles, your brother.

00:11.533 --> 00:13.317
It's vital that
we find your mom ASAP.

00:13.361 --> 00:15.058
Is there anything
we can do to help?

00:15.102 --> 00:16.190
Thought you might ask.

00:16.233 --> 00:17.408
Welcome home, Jay-Jay.

00:18.192 --> 00:19.932
We want your father,
not you.

00:19.976 --> 00:21.499
Understood, Agent Ardelia.

00:21.543 --> 00:23.023
You're under arrest.

00:23.066 --> 00:24.633
For what?

00:24.676 --> 00:27.505
For conducting
illegal activities
at your establishments.

00:27.549 --> 00:30.682
Hermione Lodge,
you're under arrest for
conspiracy to commit murder.

00:30.726 --> 00:32.423
Your own husband's.

00:32.467 --> 00:34.817
This is what I got
when I asked my dad
about that stupid game.

00:34.860 --> 00:37.167
I've been thinking about
making some changes to
this place, Mad Dog.

00:37.211 --> 00:39.865
-I want you to help me run it.
-Oh, yeah.

00:39.909 --> 00:42.172
[Archie] Fred Andrews
will always be
a part of Riverdale.

00:42.216 --> 00:43.565
I love you so much, Dad.

00:45.523 --> 00:48.483
-[door opens]
-[Jughead]
After Mr. Andrews' funeral,

00:48.526 --> 00:51.094
the rest of summer vacation
passed in a surreal haze.

00:53.096 --> 00:56.752
Betty, Veronica, and I
spent as much time
as we could with Archie.

00:58.145 --> 01:00.843
We had dinner
at Pop's every night.

01:00.886 --> 01:04.107
And every day you could tell
he was getting
better and better.

01:04.151 --> 01:06.501
I'm not saying
he wasn't still heartbroken,

01:06.544 --> 01:07.980
the entire town was,

01:08.024 --> 01:09.895
but my pal Archie's a fighter.

01:09.939 --> 01:12.594
And by the last day
of summer vacation,

01:12.637 --> 01:16.119
while the football field
was being mowed
for the new season,

01:16.163 --> 01:19.731
and the school floors
were being buffed to a shine,

01:19.775 --> 01:21.168
and banners
for the first dance

01:21.211 --> 01:22.691
of the year
were being hung,

01:22.734 --> 01:24.780
Archie was doing
what he does best.

01:25.868 --> 01:27.391
You know, Mad Dog,
I was thinking.

01:27.435 --> 01:28.871
School starts tomorrow.

01:30.307 --> 01:31.439
What if you came with me?

01:33.745 --> 01:35.225
[chuckles] Why would I do that?

01:35.269 --> 01:36.444
I don't know,
to get your diploma.

01:38.054 --> 01:39.099
Don't you want it?

01:40.274 --> 01:41.275
Hell yeah.

01:41.318 --> 01:43.407
Okay, then this is your chance.

01:43.451 --> 01:45.366
Isn't your younger brother
gonna be a freshman?

01:45.409 --> 01:46.932
I don't know, Red.

01:46.976 --> 01:48.586
After everything
I've lived through,

01:48.630 --> 01:51.111
I don't think going back to
textbooks and
cafeteria politics

01:51.154 --> 01:54.026
-is really my scene.
-Yeah.
It's not mine either.

01:54.070 --> 01:57.465
But getting that diploma
is what my dad wanted,
so I'm going to do it.

01:57.508 --> 01:59.728
Look, all I'm saying is,
we could do it together.

01:59.771 --> 02:01.382
Hell, you could even
try out for the Bulldogs.

02:01.425 --> 02:02.948
Ooh, a little pigskin.

02:02.992 --> 02:03.862
[Archie laughs]

02:03.906 --> 02:05.473
[indistinct chatter]

02:05.516 --> 02:06.430
[Betty] So, Mom missed
another check-in with you?

02:06.996 --> 02:08.128
Yes.

02:08.171 --> 02:09.868
But like I said, don't panic.

02:09.912 --> 02:11.957
This isn't the first time
she's been late
with the reports.

02:12.001 --> 02:13.394
Well, Charles,

02:13.437 --> 02:15.613
what if that means
she's been found out?

02:15.657 --> 02:17.789
Listen, until she contacts us,

02:17.833 --> 02:20.183
you should just focus on
being a high school student.

02:20.227 --> 02:21.489
I'll reach out
if anything changes.

02:24.100 --> 02:26.189
Now that your parents'
court date has been set,

02:26.233 --> 02:28.060
you need to make a decision.

02:28.104 --> 02:32.326
Are you testifying
on behalf of your mother?
Or your father? Or both?

02:32.369 --> 02:33.327
Or neither.

02:34.110 --> 02:35.155
I can be Switzerland.

02:37.244 --> 02:39.289
At the very minimum,
I recommend

02:39.333 --> 02:41.073
you issue
a statement of support.

02:41.117 --> 02:42.510
The press will want to know
where you stand with--

02:42.553 --> 02:43.946
No comment.

02:43.989 --> 02:45.643
That's my statement.

02:45.687 --> 02:47.341
Now if you'll
excuse me, Mr. Sowerberry,

02:47.384 --> 02:49.647
I have some last-minute
school supply shopping
I need to do.

02:51.519 --> 02:52.824
[Cheryl] Well, Jay-Jay,

02:52.868 --> 02:54.522
which one for
the first day of school?

02:55.262 --> 02:57.351
Rebellious white
after Labor Day

02:57.394 --> 02:59.353
or my signature red?

03:00.528 --> 03:03.139
I agree 100%.

03:04.836 --> 03:06.360
[Betty] You know,
I really can't imagine

03:06.403 --> 03:09.319
a better way to spend
our last night
of summer vacation

03:09.363 --> 03:11.365
Isn't it crazy?

03:11.408 --> 03:14.846
In just nine months,
life as we know it
will be over.

03:14.890 --> 03:16.152
No more high school.

03:16.196 --> 03:17.719
No more Blue and Gold.

03:19.068 --> 03:21.288
No more heart-to-hearts
at the lockers.

03:21.331 --> 03:23.551
Oh, B, don't be sad.

03:23.594 --> 03:25.379
I'm sorry, guys.

03:25.422 --> 03:28.730
I can't help but think
life goes by so fast.

03:28.773 --> 03:32.560
And none of us are very good
at stopping to savor it.

03:34.997 --> 03:36.520
But tonight, we will be.

03:36.564 --> 03:37.391
[Jughead] Mmm-hmm.

03:41.003 --> 03:43.005
[softly] I think
that's our cue, Archiekins.

03:48.445 --> 03:50.099
["Copycat" playing]

03:54.756 --> 03:55.931
[Betty chuckles]

03:58.368 --> 03:59.239
[door closes]

04:51.769 --> 04:53.510
[upbeat music playing]

04:53.554 --> 04:55.120
-Archie?
-Hmm?

04:55.164 --> 04:56.513
I forgot to set the alarm.
Get up.

04:56.557 --> 04:57.558
We're gonna be late.

05:02.563 --> 05:04.260
-[Veronica] You guys, wake up.
-[both] Hmm?

05:04.304 --> 05:06.784
We're gonna be late
for the first day
of senior year. Hurry up.

05:06.828 --> 05:07.872
[Betty] Oh, my God.

05:20.145 --> 05:21.451
-You're late.
-[record scratches,
music stops]

05:22.670 --> 05:24.062
And you are?

05:24.106 --> 05:26.674
I'm Principal Weatherbee's
replacement, Mr. Honey.

05:28.371 --> 05:30.373
We apologize for the tardiness,

05:30.417 --> 05:32.027
Mr. Honey,
it won't happen again.

05:33.071 --> 05:34.551
I don't know
what kind of a ship

05:34.595 --> 05:36.988
Waldo Weatherbee
was running around here,

05:37.032 --> 05:38.642
but things are going to be
different this year.

05:38.686 --> 05:39.817
We'll have order.

05:40.514 --> 05:41.428
Discipline.

05:42.080 --> 05:43.212
Consequences.

05:43.865 --> 05:45.736
Now get out of my sight.

05:55.050 --> 05:57.313
[Coach Clayton]
Okay, he sets up
the bubble screen for you,

05:57.357 --> 05:58.227
you catch...

05:58.445 --> 05:59.402
Bam!

05:59.446 --> 06:00.621
-You run like hell.
-Hmm.

06:00.664 --> 06:02.362
You're one of the fastest
we got, Mantle.

06:02.405 --> 06:03.798
Coach...

06:03.841 --> 06:05.713
Any chance we can make room
for one more Bulldog?

06:05.756 --> 06:07.323
Well, lineup's
pretty much set.

06:07.367 --> 06:09.020
-You looking to play?
-[Mad Dog] Definitely.

06:09.064 --> 06:10.195
If you'll have me
on the team, sir.

06:10.239 --> 06:11.327
So, what's your name?

06:11.371 --> 06:12.372
Munroe.

06:12.850 --> 06:13.895
Munroe Moore.

06:15.418 --> 06:16.854
Come out to practice,
show us what you got.

06:16.898 --> 06:18.378
For sure. I'll be there.

06:18.421 --> 06:19.727
This is gonna be
the best season ever.

06:29.737 --> 06:30.651
[sighs]

06:30.694 --> 06:31.826
[Kevin] I'm not too late, am I?

06:31.869 --> 06:34.481
To sign up for, uh...

06:34.524 --> 06:36.396
I don't know, I was thinking,
maybe an arts reporter?

06:36.874 --> 06:37.832
Kevin...

06:38.572 --> 06:39.486
Betty...

06:40.138 --> 06:42.576
um, I'm also here because...

06:44.491 --> 06:46.231
I've been doing
a lot of work on myself,

06:46.275 --> 06:48.799
ever since I was left behind
by the Farm,

06:48.843 --> 06:50.410
and it's helped me
to realize that

06:50.453 --> 06:52.760
I don't...
I don't need the Farm...

06:53.891 --> 06:55.415
to make me feel whole,
but I...

06:55.458 --> 06:57.242
I do need my friends.

06:57.286 --> 06:59.114
Especially my former
best friend.

07:00.115 --> 07:01.246
[sighs]

07:01.290 --> 07:02.291
I am...

07:03.161 --> 07:04.336
so sorry

07:05.120 --> 07:06.251
for the way I treated you

07:06.295 --> 07:07.688
while I was under
Edgar's spell.

07:07.731 --> 07:09.167
Oh, you mean like

07:09.211 --> 07:12.127
when you dragged me
by my ankles
to get a lobotomy?

07:13.171 --> 07:14.172
Yeah. I...

07:15.435 --> 07:17.828
I'm most ashamed of that.

07:17.872 --> 07:20.135
I hope that I can show you
how much I've changed.

07:20.178 --> 07:21.876
And I hope...

07:23.312 --> 07:25.445
that I prove to you
that you can trust me again.

07:26.184 --> 07:28.230
[sighs] Um, I...

07:28.273 --> 07:30.711
I'm so, so sorry, Betty.

07:34.497 --> 07:36.020
Just fill out
an application, Kev,

07:37.152 --> 07:38.283
and then we'll see.

07:41.548 --> 07:43.114
[Doris on PA]
Jughead Jones,

07:43.158 --> 07:45.682
please report
to the Principal's Office.

07:45.726 --> 07:48.598
Jughead Jones
to the Principal's Office.

07:48.642 --> 07:49.469
[knock on door]

07:51.035 --> 07:51.993
Am I in trouble again?

07:52.036 --> 07:53.255
No.

07:53.298 --> 07:55.170
In fact, you have a visitor.

07:55.213 --> 07:57.302
I'm Mr. Chipping.
It's nice to meet you,

07:57.564 --> 07:58.565
Jughead.

07:58.608 --> 08:00.436
Nice to meet you, too.

08:00.480 --> 08:04.135
Over the summer you submitted
a short story
to a writing contest?

08:04.179 --> 08:05.876
[sighs] Yeah. I didn't win.

08:05.920 --> 08:08.488
Yeah, I know.
I was one of the judges.

08:08.531 --> 08:10.577
And I was very impressed
with your voice.

08:10.620 --> 08:13.362
And while I couldn't
sway my fellow judges,

08:13.405 --> 08:16.496
I can offer you an opportunity

08:16.539 --> 08:17.888
to come study writing with me.

08:17.932 --> 08:21.152
I am a teacher
at Stonewall Prep.

08:21.196 --> 08:22.980
You want me to transfer to
Stonewall Prep?

08:23.024 --> 08:25.200
It's a tremendous offer,
Mr. Jones.

08:25.243 --> 08:26.897
I'm good.

08:26.941 --> 08:29.596
But thank you for the visit
and for liking my story.

08:31.859 --> 08:33.904
[Veronica] My good news
of the day is,

08:33.948 --> 08:36.211
Mrs. Burble said
I'm a shoo-in for Harvard.

08:37.429 --> 08:38.822
[chuckles] I mean, obviously.

08:38.866 --> 08:40.432
-[laughs]
-Damn.

08:40.476 --> 08:42.565
I guess I better start looking
at community colleges in...

08:42.609 --> 08:44.436
Where's Harvard?

08:44.480 --> 08:45.655
-[cameras clicking]
-[reporter 1] Veronica!
Do you think your mother

08:45.699 --> 08:47.483
really tried to have
your father killed?

08:47.527 --> 08:48.528
-Back off.
-[reporter 2] Now that that the
court dates have been set,

08:48.571 --> 08:49.267
-whose side will you choose?
-Oh, hell, no.

08:49.311 --> 08:50.442
[reporters clamoring]

08:52.009 --> 08:53.576
I am not having
my senior year ruined

08:53.620 --> 08:55.926
by a bunch of
bloodsucking paparazzi.

08:55.970 --> 08:58.581
[clamoring continues]

08:58.625 --> 09:00.496
-Screw it.
-[fire alarm ringing]

09:00.540 --> 09:01.366
Archie...

09:03.281 --> 09:04.805
So much for
a quiet senior year.

09:18.253 --> 09:21.386
Mr. Honey,
thank you for meeting with us.

09:21.430 --> 09:24.215
I, Cheryl Blossom,
as Student Body President,

09:24.259 --> 09:26.043
and Antoinette Topaz

09:26.087 --> 09:28.437
as Acting Student Body
Vice-President,

09:28.480 --> 09:31.092
would like to
personally welcome you
to Riverdale High.

09:32.006 --> 09:33.573
Thank you, ladies.

09:34.748 --> 09:36.576
I was actually going to
reach out to you,

09:36.619 --> 09:39.927
regarding that Back to School
Dance that you've organized.

09:40.623 --> 09:41.885
It's canceled.

09:41.929 --> 09:43.539
For why?

09:43.583 --> 09:45.454
At the last student dance,
multiple students
were murdered.

09:45.497 --> 09:46.803
Yes.

09:46.847 --> 09:49.501
But that's exactly why
we need this dance,

09:50.111 --> 09:50.938
to heal.

09:51.721 --> 09:52.853
Mr. Honey,

09:52.896 --> 09:55.072
if I may speak
from personal experience,

09:56.291 --> 09:59.207
the Back to School Dance,
after my brother Jason's death,

10:00.034 --> 10:02.340
provided much needed catharsis.

10:03.124 --> 10:04.604
Hmm. Well, I disagree.

10:09.434 --> 10:12.089
Now, I will only
repeat myself once.

10:12.133 --> 10:15.745
There will be
no Back to School dance.

10:23.144 --> 10:24.754
[Archie] Huddle up, guys.

10:24.798 --> 10:27.104
All right, Munroe,
let's see if we can
catch them napping.

10:27.148 --> 10:28.540
-On one. Ready?
-[teammates] Break!

10:31.718 --> 10:33.763
Watch your man!

10:33.807 --> 10:37.506
Attaboy, Reggie!
Don't give 'em an ounce
of daylight, all right?

10:37.549 --> 10:38.550
Come on. You hear me?

10:39.247 --> 10:40.509
[Archie] Blue, 34.

10:40.552 --> 10:42.076
Blue, 34.

10:42.119 --> 10:43.773
Down. Set. Hut!

10:51.651 --> 10:52.521
[player] Come on!

10:53.783 --> 10:56.133
-[players cheering]
-[exhales deeply]

10:59.571 --> 11:00.398
[Marty] Hey!

11:00.964 --> 11:01.835
Get over here.

11:02.792 --> 11:03.793
Now!

11:10.495 --> 11:11.627
Get over here!

11:11.671 --> 11:12.976
What are you doing?

11:13.020 --> 11:15.196
That guy just made you
look like a damned fool.

11:15.762 --> 11:17.111
He's fast.

11:17.154 --> 11:18.547
[Marty] It's unacceptable.

11:18.590 --> 11:21.376
That was
an embarrassing display.

11:21.419 --> 11:23.030
Go out there. Come on, man.

11:23.813 --> 11:24.858
Show me somethin'.

11:35.129 --> 11:36.173
[camera clicks]

11:38.219 --> 11:39.176
What the hell?

11:41.570 --> 11:43.703
Oh, you have
gotta be kidding me.

11:45.226 --> 11:47.271
Vixens!

11:47.315 --> 11:50.840
This pervert was
taking pictures of us
while we changed.

11:50.884 --> 11:54.061
Collecting photos for your sad,
pubescent spank bank, are you?

11:55.453 --> 11:57.151
No! No.

11:57.194 --> 12:00.763
A reporter
from Rumordale.com
reached out, and he told me

12:00.807 --> 12:03.287
he would pay 500 bucks
for a photo of Veronica.

12:03.331 --> 12:05.028
How am I supposed to
say no to that?

12:05.072 --> 12:07.074
You just say it, you worm.

12:11.905 --> 12:13.210
Nice job out there, Mad Dog.

12:14.211 --> 12:15.169
Thanks.

12:15.212 --> 12:16.518
It's Munroe, actually.

12:16.561 --> 12:18.868
Oh, my bad.
I thought it was Mad Dog.

12:18.912 --> 12:20.652
Or is that just
what they called you in jail?

12:24.526 --> 12:25.745
It was juvie.

12:25.788 --> 12:27.485
And your boy Archie
was right there with me.

12:27.529 --> 12:28.748
Look, is there a problem, guys?

12:28.791 --> 12:29.879
No, bro, we're cool.

12:30.967 --> 12:32.708
But settle a bet.

12:32.752 --> 12:35.624
In prison showers,
is it true what they say
about dropping the soap?

12:37.800 --> 12:39.280
He's not worth it, dude.
Trust me.

12:45.982 --> 12:47.331
What the hell
is wrong with you?

12:47.375 --> 12:49.333
What do you think, Andrews?

12:49.377 --> 12:51.596
I've been captain
of the Bulldogs
since sophomore year.

12:51.640 --> 12:54.904
I don't need some ex-con
who showed up last-minute
stealing my thunder.

12:54.948 --> 12:57.559
Look, I saw your dad
giving you a hard time,
but man up, Reg.

12:57.602 --> 12:58.560
You're supposed to be captain.

13:05.480 --> 13:06.655
-Hey.
-[FP] Hey.

13:07.874 --> 13:09.963
Jug, you know Mr. Chipping.

13:10.006 --> 13:12.182
He was just telling me
about an offer
that he made you.

13:12.226 --> 13:13.923
Yeah. Uh...

13:13.967 --> 13:15.446
My answer still hasn't changed.

13:15.490 --> 13:17.579
I'm sorry, Mr. Chipping,
but I can't go to your school.

13:18.885 --> 13:21.365
If this is about money,
I got a few bucks socked away.

13:21.409 --> 13:23.193
No. It's not just about money.

13:23.237 --> 13:24.934
Boy, look me
in the eye and tell me

13:24.978 --> 13:27.154
you don't want to go
to a school
that recognizes your talent.

13:28.633 --> 13:30.244
[Mr. Chipping]
Jug, how about this?

13:30.287 --> 13:32.594
How about you come take a tour,
see the place for yourself,

13:32.637 --> 13:34.465
and then make the decision.

13:34.509 --> 13:37.425
-I know. I...
I just don't want to--
-You're taking the damn tour.

13:38.905 --> 13:39.862
Have a seat.

13:40.341 --> 13:41.211
[sighs]

13:44.736 --> 13:46.303
[Betty] Charles, I'm back.

13:46.347 --> 13:49.176
They ran out of
fortune cookies,
if you can believe it.

13:51.047 --> 13:52.005
Charles?

14:16.943 --> 14:18.031
Wait. What?

14:20.947 --> 14:22.905
Is this what you do
when I'm not around, Betty?

14:22.949 --> 14:24.689
You read
classified information?

14:24.733 --> 14:27.562
When were you gonna tell me
that you had Kevin
under surveillance?

14:27.954 --> 14:29.869
I wasn't.

14:29.912 --> 14:32.697
From the get-go, I suspected
Kevin hadn't fully
cut ties with the Farm.

14:32.741 --> 14:35.613
I started monitoring
his phone activity,
and it turns out

14:35.657 --> 14:36.788
he's been texting with
Fangs Fogarty.

14:39.879 --> 14:40.880
[sighs]

14:40.923 --> 14:41.881
I'm...

14:43.578 --> 14:46.059
I mean, I was hoping that
Kevin was done

14:47.060 --> 14:47.974
with the Farm.

14:48.017 --> 14:50.324
It seemed like he was done.

14:50.367 --> 14:52.369
This might be
a blessing in disguise.

14:52.413 --> 14:54.589
We could use the relationship
to our advantage.

14:55.068 --> 14:56.156
In his texts,

14:56.199 --> 14:57.679
Kevin keeps pushing
to meet in person,

14:57.722 --> 14:59.507
but Fangs has been
holding him off, saying

14:59.550 --> 15:02.336
he can't risk it
unless he has something
useful to offer in return.

15:02.379 --> 15:03.903
So...

15:03.946 --> 15:05.948
What if we
accidentally let slip--

15:05.992 --> 15:09.691
Some fake intel
about our investigation
in front of Kevin?

15:09.996 --> 15:11.345
Exactly.

15:11.388 --> 15:14.000
Something that'll lure
Fangs out of hiding.

15:14.043 --> 15:16.306
The first step is to
develop Kevin as an asset.

15:17.307 --> 15:18.308
Think you can do that?

15:19.875 --> 15:20.876
100%.

15:23.879 --> 15:24.793
Cheryl?

15:31.626 --> 15:33.236
-[creaks]
-[gasps]

15:33.280 --> 15:34.281
Oh, you scared me.

15:35.412 --> 15:36.326
What were you doing in there?

15:38.546 --> 15:39.547
I was...

15:39.895 --> 15:41.114
praying.

15:41.157 --> 15:42.854
Since when are you religious?

15:42.898 --> 15:45.945
I was looking for
some divine guidance
on how to handle this

15:45.988 --> 15:47.816
discord with Mr. Honey,

15:47.859 --> 15:52.908
and the spirits
didn't fail to deliver
a hellaciously simple idea.

15:52.952 --> 15:55.302
Instead of throwing
a Back to School Dance,

15:55.345 --> 15:57.608
we are hosting
a Back to School party

15:58.609 --> 16:00.655
right here at Thistlehouse.

16:05.138 --> 16:06.835
["Archie's Party" playing]

16:08.489 --> 16:10.012
♪ Archie's gonna be there

16:10.056 --> 16:11.753
♪ Jughead's gonna be there

16:11.796 --> 16:14.016
♪ Reggie's gonna be there too

16:15.670 --> 16:18.281
♪ Hey, Archie's parties are
Out of sight ♪

16:18.325 --> 16:19.848
♪ Out of sight

16:19.891 --> 16:22.024
♪ He's going to have one
On Friday night ♪

16:22.068 --> 16:23.547
♪ Friday night

16:23.591 --> 16:26.333
♪ Pick you up
About half past eight... ♪

16:26.376 --> 16:30.076
Your name may be Honey,
but I will always be
the queen bee.

16:30.119 --> 16:31.860
You have no power over me.

16:31.903 --> 16:33.775
♪ ...gonna be there too

16:34.776 --> 16:36.691
♪ Betty's gonna be there

16:36.734 --> 16:39.041
♪ You and me
Will be there too ♪

16:43.785 --> 16:45.265
Hey, are you Forsythe?

16:45.308 --> 16:46.483
Yeah.

16:46.527 --> 16:48.311
Bret Weston Wallis.

16:48.355 --> 16:50.661
Mr. Chipping asked me
to roll out the red carpet.

16:50.705 --> 16:51.793
You can just call me Jughead.

16:51.836 --> 16:52.924
I prefer Forsythe.

16:53.403 --> 16:54.317
Who's your friend?

16:54.361 --> 16:55.579
Betty Cooper.

16:55.623 --> 16:56.711
Cute. Very...

16:57.451 --> 16:58.669
Sweet Valley High.

16:58.713 --> 17:00.323
Let me give you some stats.

17:00.367 --> 17:06.155
Our faculty holds
132 master's degrees
and 28 doctoral degrees,

17:06.199 --> 17:07.983
which sounds impressive,

17:08.027 --> 17:10.029
but the truth is,
most of our teachers
are hopelessly out of touch.

17:10.855 --> 17:12.596
Except for Mr. Chipping,
he's cool.

17:12.640 --> 17:14.337
And I'm not just saying that
because he's coming
right behind me.

17:14.381 --> 17:15.773
Mr. Chipping, how's it hanging?

17:15.817 --> 17:17.775
[Mr. Chipping]
Bret, don't let me
interrupt you.

17:17.819 --> 17:21.649
But I wanted to invite Jughead
to sit in on a salon with us.

17:21.692 --> 17:24.086
If I'm not mistaken,
we're focusing on
Moby-Dicktomorrow?

17:24.130 --> 17:26.001
Oh, great.
That's one of my favorites.

17:26.045 --> 17:27.263
See you tomorrow, Mr. Jones.

17:27.307 --> 17:28.525
Definitely.

17:28.569 --> 17:30.049
Betty, you can come, too.

17:30.092 --> 17:31.920
I bet you've got a lot to say
about Moby-Dick.

17:33.095 --> 17:35.750
No. No, I don't.

17:35.793 --> 17:38.753
And I think I've gotten
my fill of this place
already, so...

17:39.797 --> 17:41.060
It is a lot to digest.

17:41.799 --> 17:43.671
Speaking of which,
in the cafeteria

17:43.714 --> 17:46.065
we've got vegan, keto vegan,
raw keto vegan...

17:51.200 --> 17:52.245
I don't like drama,

17:52.941 --> 17:54.073
Ms. Lodge.

17:54.769 --> 17:55.900
Neither do I,

17:56.466 --> 17:57.859
Mr. Honey.

17:57.902 --> 18:01.689
And yet, there's this article
on Rumordale.com

18:01.732 --> 18:04.474
published about you
this morning,
promising drama.

18:05.388 --> 18:06.563
I'm assuming
you've read that.

18:06.781 --> 18:08.391
No.

18:08.435 --> 18:10.915
I've been avoiding the tabloids
these past few months.

18:10.959 --> 18:16.269
An unnamed inside source
that worked at your nightclub
is claiming that

18:16.312 --> 18:18.097
you, in fact,

18:18.140 --> 18:21.100
are responsible for the crimes
that your father
allegedly committed.

18:31.284 --> 18:32.285
Fascinating.

18:33.547 --> 18:35.070
Your point, Mr. Honey?

18:35.114 --> 18:36.767
I was just wondering
if you shouldn't

18:37.638 --> 18:40.380
take a sabbatical
from Riverdale High,

18:40.423 --> 18:42.512
until you can get all these
personal matters of yours

18:43.383 --> 18:44.210
sorted.

18:49.998 --> 18:51.304
-[doo-wop music playing]
-[Kevin and Betty laughing]

18:52.218 --> 18:53.523
Oh, man...

18:53.567 --> 18:55.438
I have missed
hanging out with you, Betty.

18:55.482 --> 18:57.179
I was thinking back
to freshman year.

18:57.223 --> 18:59.312
You would talk about
crushing on Archie...

18:59.355 --> 19:01.227
[Betty laughs]

19:01.270 --> 19:03.272
...and I'd talk about
whatever weird Grind'Em
hook-up I'd just had.

19:03.316 --> 19:05.448
-Or not had.
-I remember.

19:11.019 --> 19:14.501
Kev, I think
the reason
I was cold earlier...

19:17.373 --> 19:19.288
I mean...

19:19.332 --> 19:23.727
as you know,
my mom and Polly are
still at the Farm.

19:23.771 --> 19:26.426
And my half-brother is
investigating them.

19:26.469 --> 19:28.210
Yeah. Um...

19:28.254 --> 19:29.385
-Charles?
-Yeah.

19:29.429 --> 19:31.866
-Right? Yeah.
-Anyways, today, finally,

19:33.084 --> 19:34.564
there was a break in the case.

19:35.913 --> 19:38.002
Really? What?

19:38.046 --> 19:44.618
The FBI found a witness
who's willing to
testify against the Farm.

19:44.661 --> 19:46.010
Hmm.

19:46.054 --> 19:48.796
Charles says it may
finally break open the case.

19:49.536 --> 19:50.537
-Wow.
-Yeah.

19:51.059 --> 19:52.191
That is...

19:54.410 --> 19:55.368
Cheers.

19:58.371 --> 20:00.373
[rustling]

20:04.290 --> 20:05.204
Kevin?

20:06.248 --> 20:07.554
[laughs] Fangs, hey.

20:10.687 --> 20:11.949
Can I at least hug you?

20:12.472 --> 20:14.691
I... I miss you so much.

20:14.735 --> 20:16.040
I've missed you too.

20:18.086 --> 20:20.001
But first you said you had
some information for me?

20:20.044 --> 20:21.307
Yeah. There's, uh...

20:22.090 --> 20:23.874
There's a witness.

20:23.918 --> 20:26.312
The FBI found someone
who's ready to come forward
against Edgar.

20:26.355 --> 20:27.226
Who's the witness?

20:29.010 --> 20:30.446
I... I don't... I don't know.

20:30.490 --> 20:32.100
-I didn't get a name.
-[sighs]

20:32.143 --> 20:33.928
But...

20:33.971 --> 20:37.845
Information's not
the only reason why
you wanted to meet me, right?

20:37.888 --> 20:41.065
Kevin, Edgar and
the rest of the Farm
don't think you can be trusted.

20:42.415 --> 20:45.722
Of course,
I mean, if you found out
who the witness was...

20:45.766 --> 20:47.246
I mean,
that might change things.

20:47.289 --> 20:48.159
Get the name...

20:48.769 --> 20:49.944
and then we can be together.

20:50.597 --> 20:52.120
Uh, yeah. I'll try.

20:52.425 --> 20:53.295
Good.

20:54.601 --> 20:56.603
[sighs]
You know how to reach me.

21:02.913 --> 21:03.958
[exhales]

21:07.266 --> 21:08.136
Betty--

21:08.179 --> 21:09.964
You are so messed up, Kevin.

21:12.749 --> 21:15.317
Reggie,
Mr. Honey is riding my ass

21:15.361 --> 21:18.015
about this article
on Rumordale.com.

21:18.668 --> 21:20.888
About me. About La Bonne Nuit.

21:20.931 --> 21:23.369
An "inside source"
with "intimate knowledge"

21:23.412 --> 21:26.459
of my businesses claims that
I'm the criminal kingpin,
not my father.

21:26.981 --> 21:28.069
Was it you, Reggie?

21:28.112 --> 21:30.680
Are you the "inside source"?

21:30.724 --> 21:32.291
Is that why you're hiding
behind those shades?

21:34.641 --> 21:36.469
I didn't say a word
to the press...

21:36.512 --> 21:38.427
Oh, my God. Reggie, your eye.

21:38.471 --> 21:40.299
...but maybe you should ask
your old man.

21:44.172 --> 21:46.217
[Archie] So? Did Reggie admit
to leaking the story?

21:46.653 --> 21:47.654
No.

21:48.394 --> 21:49.308
He didn't do it.

21:52.267 --> 21:53.224
Archie...

21:54.356 --> 21:55.749
Reggie had a black eye.

21:57.185 --> 21:59.013
And it wasn't
the first time, either.

21:59.622 --> 22:01.145
From practice, you mean?

22:01.189 --> 22:02.059
No.

22:02.538 --> 22:03.844
No. I think...

22:05.280 --> 22:06.150
[sighs]

22:06.194 --> 22:07.021
No. I know.

22:10.024 --> 22:11.417
Reggie's dad hits him.

22:20.948 --> 22:22.079
Kevin,

22:22.123 --> 22:23.385
you lied to me.

22:23.429 --> 22:25.169
You told me that
you wanted to be my friend,

22:25.213 --> 22:26.997
and then you go out
into the woods

22:27.041 --> 22:30.218
for some secret tryst
with your cult boyfriend.

22:30.261 --> 22:31.350
I'm... I'm sorry

22:31.872 --> 22:34.135
for... for everything.

22:34.178 --> 22:36.355
I truly do
miss being your friend.

22:36.398 --> 22:38.661
You betrayed Betty
after she gave you a chance.

22:38.705 --> 22:42.230
Yeah. [stammering]
I wasn't thinking clearly,
I just wanted to see Fangs.

22:42.273 --> 22:44.101
No. No. You wanted to
trade information,

22:44.145 --> 22:47.017
-so you can get back
in the good graces of the Farm.
-No!

22:47.061 --> 22:48.845
-You're still one of them.
-I'm not, I swear.

22:48.889 --> 22:50.194
I'm not a part of anything.

22:50.238 --> 22:51.631
And you... You, Betty,

22:51.674 --> 22:54.285
you ignored me
all summer, okay?

22:54.329 --> 22:55.852
And I understand,

22:55.896 --> 22:57.114
but I was alone.

22:58.420 --> 23:00.161
At least Fangs texted me back.

23:01.815 --> 23:02.903
He's all I have.

23:03.730 --> 23:04.557
[Kevin sighs]

23:06.907 --> 23:07.908
Can we have a word?

23:20.573 --> 23:22.401
He's useless.
We got to cut him loose.

23:22.444 --> 23:23.793
No, Charles. I...

23:24.664 --> 23:26.970
I believe Kevin, okay?

23:27.014 --> 23:28.537
I saw them in the woods.

23:28.581 --> 23:29.843
I think he'll help us.

23:29.886 --> 23:31.192
No. We're not going to get
anywhere with him.

23:31.235 --> 23:32.106
He's traumatized.

23:32.846 --> 23:33.847
He's lonely.

23:34.456 --> 23:36.023
Listen, I'm sorry, Betty.

23:36.066 --> 23:37.590
We'll find another way
to get Alice back.

23:38.547 --> 23:39.418
[whistle blows]

23:40.201 --> 23:41.158
[Marty] Let's go, Reggie!

23:41.202 --> 23:42.290
Blue, 18.

23:42.986 --> 23:44.161
Blue, 18.

23:45.380 --> 23:47.338
Down. Set. Hut!

23:51.560 --> 23:52.474
[boy] Get it. Get it. Get it!

23:53.475 --> 23:55.216
-[groans]
-[Marty] All, come on!

23:55.259 --> 23:56.913
[whistle blows]

23:56.957 --> 23:59.002
All right, guys,
hit the shower.
Practice is over.

24:01.614 --> 24:03.920
[Marty] Hey!
Get over here.

24:04.704 --> 24:06.401
What the hell are you doing?

24:06.445 --> 24:07.968
I had it, Dad. It just slipped.

24:08.011 --> 24:09.665
It slipped?

24:09.709 --> 24:11.580
It won't happen again,
I promise.

24:11.624 --> 24:13.930
If it does, so help me,

24:13.974 --> 24:15.062
-I'll--
-[Archie] What?

24:16.498 --> 24:17.934
You're gonna hit him again?

24:17.978 --> 24:19.458
Give him another black eye?

24:19.501 --> 24:20.371
What the hell
have you been saying?

24:20.415 --> 24:21.547
Nothing, Dad.

24:21.590 --> 24:23.418
Andrews, this is none
of your business.

24:23.462 --> 24:25.681
Reggie works his ass off
on this field
while you stand here and yell.

24:25.725 --> 24:27.204
We all have to listen to it.

24:27.248 --> 24:28.292
So, get the hell out of here.

24:28.336 --> 24:29.772
Go. Or I'll
throw you out myself.

24:29.816 --> 24:32.471
Back off, Andrews. I mean it.

24:32.514 --> 24:34.690
Reggie, your dad has no right
to treat you like this.

24:36.518 --> 24:38.215
-[Munroe] Hey.
-[Coach Clayton] Hey, hey.
Knock it off, you two.

24:38.259 --> 24:39.608
-Hey. Hey!
-Knock it off.

24:39.652 --> 24:41.175
-Knock it off.
-Dead to me, Andrews.

24:42.524 --> 24:43.482
Dead!

24:49.792 --> 24:50.663
Go.

24:51.011 --> 24:52.012
Go!

24:56.364 --> 24:57.278
[school bell rings]

24:59.193 --> 25:00.542
[Bret] Hey, Forsythe.

25:00.586 --> 25:02.457
Guys, this is that kid
from Riverdale.

25:02.501 --> 25:04.807
Forsythe, this is Donna,
Jonathan, Joan.

25:04.851 --> 25:06.983
Good afternoon,
seekers of knowledge!

25:07.680 --> 25:08.898
Why are we not sitting?

25:12.380 --> 25:14.295
Now then, Moby-Dick.

25:15.905 --> 25:16.950
Hmm?

25:16.993 --> 25:18.517
It's well done.

25:18.560 --> 25:20.127
Obviously.

25:20.170 --> 25:23.739
But it highlights a problem
that I have with the syllabus.

25:23.783 --> 25:26.089
Do we really need to
hear this narrative again?

25:26.133 --> 25:29.136
Right. Because the only authors
we're allowed to like now

25:29.179 --> 25:31.138
are those who
lived an unblemished life.

25:31.181 --> 25:32.313
I'm fine with that.

25:32.356 --> 25:34.968
Guys, guys, guys.
Let's get back on topic.

25:35.011 --> 25:39.407
Now, what do you think
that the whale symbolizes?

25:40.321 --> 25:41.148
Nothing.

25:44.891 --> 25:47.197
Care to elaborate
on that, Mr. Jones?

25:50.505 --> 25:54.553
Well, it's
pretty well-established
that Melville hated allegory.

25:54.596 --> 25:56.772
And he's quoted as saying
that his biggest fear was

25:56.816 --> 25:58.818
Moby-Dickwould be
seen as a fable.

25:58.861 --> 25:59.732
[Mr. Chipping] Any rebuttals?

26:03.910 --> 26:05.564
[door buzzing]

26:10.481 --> 26:12.483
Breaking out the blonde wig,
I see.

26:12.527 --> 26:14.877
Yes, that's the only way
I can get around

26:14.921 --> 26:16.705
without being harassed
by the paparazzi.

26:17.097 --> 26:18.533
But then...

26:18.577 --> 26:21.188
you'd know all about that,
wouldn't you?

26:21.231 --> 26:23.407
Oh, are you receiving
some blowback

26:23.451 --> 26:25.322
from lying through your teeth
to get me arrested?

26:25.888 --> 26:26.715
How unfortunate.

26:27.629 --> 26:29.588
Why did you leak the story?

26:29.631 --> 26:32.068
Was it a desperate ploy
to get me to come see you?

26:32.112 --> 26:34.593
Mija,I'm not paying
for your crimes.

26:35.289 --> 26:36.943
I merely told the truth.

26:36.986 --> 26:39.249
I told the world what you are,

26:40.294 --> 26:41.121
a Lodge,

26:42.078 --> 26:42.905
through and through.

26:45.386 --> 26:46.474
Deal with it.

26:49.259 --> 26:50.086
[door buzzing]

26:50.870 --> 26:52.785
["Cross Me" playing]

27:06.276 --> 27:08.844
-[glass clinking]
-[man] Whoo!

27:08.888 --> 27:12.065
My esteemed guests,
may I have
your attention please?

27:12.108 --> 27:15.329
Students of Riverdale,
we have a new enemy
in our midst.

27:15.372 --> 27:17.505
This killjoy is
our new principal,
Mr. Honey.

27:18.332 --> 27:19.899
[crowd booing]

27:19.942 --> 27:22.728
However, never fear.

27:22.771 --> 27:24.599
I, as your
student body president,

27:24.643 --> 27:27.994
will make sure
that he is beheaded
by Homecoming,

27:28.037 --> 27:30.779
or my name
isn't Cheryl Marjorie Blossom.

27:30.823 --> 27:32.563
[all cheering]

27:32.607 --> 27:34.174
["Cross Me" continues playing]

27:40.833 --> 27:42.399
-[Jughead] Your drinks, ladies.
-Thank you.

27:42.443 --> 27:43.400
[Veronica thanks in French]

27:43.444 --> 27:45.141
So...

27:45.185 --> 27:47.056
What's this I hear
about you transferring?

27:48.318 --> 27:51.713
Jug is being recruited
by Stonewall Prep.

27:51.757 --> 27:54.237
How was the salon today,
by the way?

27:54.281 --> 27:56.065
Shocked to say, I actually
kind of enjoyed it.

27:56.109 --> 27:58.720
And the kids had
actually read Moby-Dick.

27:58.764 --> 28:00.026
Jughead,

28:00.069 --> 28:02.115
there is no school
more nihilistic

28:02.158 --> 28:03.943
and/or privileged
than Stonewall.

28:03.986 --> 28:07.381
Besides, why would you
want to leave
your lovely girlfriend here?

28:07.424 --> 28:09.426
Jug, we would make
anything work.

28:09.905 --> 28:11.472
Okay?

28:11.515 --> 28:12.952
But I would miss you.

28:12.995 --> 28:14.301
[Veronica]
Trust me when I say,

28:14.867 --> 28:16.782
you would be miserable.

28:16.825 --> 28:18.305
I'm just trying to keep
an open mind, is all.

28:19.567 --> 28:20.568
Hmm.

28:21.047 --> 28:22.526
[panting]

28:23.832 --> 28:24.877
[groans]

28:30.273 --> 28:31.840
[Cheryl] Excuse me?

28:31.884 --> 28:33.102
What are you doing down here?

28:34.103 --> 28:36.018
-What's up?
-This hallway is off-limits.

28:36.062 --> 28:38.847
The locked door
at the top of the stairs
should've been a hint.

28:38.891 --> 28:41.197
Yeah. The line
to the bathroom
was too long.

28:41.241 --> 28:42.590
Was looking for another one.

28:42.633 --> 28:44.723
Then get thee to the barn
with the other animals.

28:53.514 --> 28:55.255
-[indistinct chatter]
-[music playing]

28:57.692 --> 28:58.737
Kev...

28:58.780 --> 28:59.738
Hey.

29:00.826 --> 29:01.783
Hey.

29:03.959 --> 29:07.397
I'm sorry
that we interrogated you.

29:07.441 --> 29:09.356
It's okay. I get it.

29:09.399 --> 29:10.749
You're trying to save your mom.

29:12.533 --> 29:13.490
Yeah.

29:19.105 --> 29:20.541
What I'm about to tell you

29:22.108 --> 29:24.675
puts everything on the line,

29:24.719 --> 29:26.634
but I believe in you.

29:28.462 --> 29:29.593
What are you talking about?

29:29.637 --> 29:30.551
[inhales deeply]

29:33.119 --> 29:34.903
My mom isn't just at the Farm,

29:36.731 --> 29:39.516
she's undercover at the Farm.

29:39.560 --> 29:42.171
She's been sending us
messages all summer,
but she stopped.

29:42.215 --> 29:44.130
And I'm worried that
she may be in trouble.

29:45.218 --> 29:46.959
Oh, my God, Betty...

29:47.002 --> 29:49.918
And I know that
you can turn around
and tell Fangs everything,

29:49.962 --> 29:52.268
but I'm choosing to believe
that our friendship

29:52.312 --> 29:55.054
runs deeper
than Edgar's brainwashing.

29:55.097 --> 29:56.577
It... It...

29:56.620 --> 29:57.447
It does.

29:57.883 --> 29:58.797
Kev...

30:00.189 --> 30:02.801
I need you to ask Fangs
to meet with you again,

30:02.844 --> 30:04.715
so he can tell you
where Edgar is hiding.

30:04.759 --> 30:05.978
He won't.

30:06.021 --> 30:08.197
He will if you have
information to give him.

30:08.241 --> 30:10.286
Like the name
of the FBI witness,

30:10.330 --> 30:12.680
who doesn't actually exist,
by the way.

30:12.723 --> 30:14.508
But we can give him
a fake name.

30:16.336 --> 30:17.206
Like who?

30:17.250 --> 30:19.078
Like Penelope Blossom.

30:19.121 --> 30:21.732
Kev, will you do this?
Will you help me?

30:22.690 --> 30:23.909
Will you help my mom?

30:24.823 --> 30:26.172
Of course, Betty.

30:28.696 --> 30:29.958
[music playing]

30:32.047 --> 30:32.874
Yo.

30:33.570 --> 30:35.659
Who invited you, new guy?

30:35.703 --> 30:37.400
Dude, Reggie, lay off.

30:38.010 --> 30:39.011
Cheryl,

30:39.707 --> 30:41.274
you know this guy?

30:41.317 --> 30:44.103
No, but I certainly don't
object to him being here,

30:44.146 --> 30:45.669
which is more
than I can say for you.

30:45.713 --> 30:46.975
So what you're saying is...

30:47.802 --> 30:49.151
Mad Dog here crashed.

30:49.195 --> 30:50.718
-[tires screech]
-[siren wailing]

30:52.067 --> 30:53.895
Wonderful. And now
the po-po has arrived.

30:53.939 --> 30:55.549
[police radio chatter]

30:55.592 --> 30:57.072
[FP] Party's over.

30:57.116 --> 30:58.117
Everybody go home.

30:59.161 --> 31:00.293
Go home. Move.

31:00.902 --> 31:02.904
[indistinct chatter]

31:02.948 --> 31:06.168
Jughead, boy,
you better not be drinking
whatever's in that cup.

31:08.431 --> 31:09.389
[Reggie] Sheriff Jones.

31:09.432 --> 31:11.043
Someone get this man a beer.

31:11.086 --> 31:13.306
You want to see the inside
of the drunk tank
tonight, Mantle?

31:13.349 --> 31:14.524
I'll take him home, Mr. Jones.

31:16.875 --> 31:18.485
What are the charges,
Sheriff Jones,

31:18.528 --> 31:19.660
if one might ask?

31:20.574 --> 31:22.402
Someone called the station
about the noise.

31:22.445 --> 31:23.969
Impossible.

31:24.012 --> 31:26.885
All of Thistlehouse's neighbors
are either deaf or dead.

31:26.928 --> 31:28.887
Who exactly made
this absurd complaint?

31:28.930 --> 31:30.062
Someone named, uh...

31:30.714 --> 31:31.541
Honey.

31:32.064 --> 31:33.065
Party's over, Cheryl.

31:42.988 --> 31:44.815
Reg, I think I already know,

31:45.599 --> 31:46.905
but how did you get
the black eye?

31:49.820 --> 31:51.039
What do you want me to say?

31:51.648 --> 31:52.519
Huh?

31:54.042 --> 31:57.002
That my dad hits me?

31:57.045 --> 32:00.266
That he beats
the crap out of me
over the stupidest things?

32:00.309 --> 32:03.486
That he's been doing it for
as long as I can remember?

32:05.967 --> 32:07.534
I'm sorry, Reg. I really am.

32:10.624 --> 32:14.149
I was always so jealous
of the relationship
you had with your dad.

32:14.193 --> 32:16.151
No matter what
you wanted to do,

32:16.195 --> 32:17.457
he always stuck by you.

32:18.632 --> 32:20.851
I have no idea
what that feels like.

32:25.508 --> 32:27.075
And when your dad died,

32:28.990 --> 32:31.036
all I kept thinking was,

32:31.079 --> 32:33.081
what if it had been
my old man instead?

32:42.134 --> 32:43.744
Listen, what can we do?

32:43.787 --> 32:44.919
Or what can I do?

32:44.963 --> 32:46.355
You've already done
enough, man.

32:47.095 --> 32:48.183
You called him out.

32:49.793 --> 32:50.838
Now, it's on me.

32:54.407 --> 32:55.712
I gotta take a stand.

32:57.366 --> 32:58.541
So, what are you thinking?

33:03.111 --> 33:04.417
[Archie] Bro,
are you sure about this?

33:06.854 --> 33:09.422
Sometimes I think
he loves this car
more than he does me.

33:10.510 --> 33:12.425
I mean, you could just...
You could talk to him.

33:13.034 --> 33:13.992
I've tried.

33:14.514 --> 33:15.558
He doesn't listen.

33:17.734 --> 33:19.345
It's time he starts to listen.

33:25.699 --> 33:27.309
Holy hell, Reg.

33:27.353 --> 33:28.702
That'll bring this to a head.

33:29.920 --> 33:32.619
It's okay, Archie.
I outweigh him by 50 pounds.

33:42.194 --> 33:43.847
[Miss Haggly] Okay, everyone.

33:43.891 --> 33:46.372
I trust you all completed
your summer reading?

33:50.289 --> 33:53.466
Who wants to read the
first section out loud for us?

33:55.903 --> 33:56.947
Anyone?

33:59.080 --> 34:00.255
All righty then.

34:00.951 --> 34:01.865
I'll start and...

34:02.866 --> 34:03.911
you follow along.

34:04.738 --> 34:06.044
"Understanding Literature,

34:07.393 --> 34:08.655
Chapter Six.

34:09.134 --> 34:11.266
English Drama.

34:11.310 --> 34:16.576
One of the great works
of the Elizabethan Age,
Romeo and Juliet,

34:17.751 --> 34:19.840
is a tragic romance,

34:21.189 --> 34:25.628
emblematic
of both Shakespeare's--"

34:25.672 --> 34:26.760
I can't take this.

34:26.803 --> 34:27.804
[Miss Haggly]
"...early period..."

34:27.848 --> 34:29.067
Come with me, right now.

34:29.110 --> 34:30.503
"...and of western drama

34:31.286 --> 34:34.072
in the 16th
and 17th centuries."

34:35.943 --> 34:37.336
Okay. What's going on?

34:37.379 --> 34:39.512
You should go to
Stonewall Prep, Jug.

34:40.252 --> 34:42.036
I hate saying that,

34:42.080 --> 34:44.647
but it's the chance
of a lifetime
and you should take it. Okay?

34:44.691 --> 34:47.041
So, you should go
before I change my mind.

34:47.085 --> 34:48.390
But what about--

34:48.434 --> 34:50.088
Don't worry about us,
we'll make it work.

34:50.131 --> 34:51.741
We've been through way worse.

34:51.785 --> 34:52.916
Just go pack up your stuff.

34:52.960 --> 34:54.396
I'll handle
everything here, okay?

34:58.226 --> 34:59.532
Go. Run.

35:05.973 --> 35:07.148
[sighs]

35:07.192 --> 35:08.628
How'd your old man
react to his car?

35:10.282 --> 35:11.283
Uh...

35:12.458 --> 35:14.851
It... It did what
it was supposed to do.

35:16.244 --> 35:17.419
It got us talking.

35:17.463 --> 35:19.117
And I said some things
he needed to hear.

35:19.726 --> 35:21.380
And I...

35:21.423 --> 35:23.817
I don't think he'll be coming
around to practices anymore.

35:29.866 --> 35:30.867
Bros?

35:32.130 --> 35:33.131
Bros for life.

35:41.748 --> 35:42.836
-[reporters clamoring]
-[cameras clicking]

35:45.534 --> 35:46.535
[banging on door]

35:47.928 --> 35:48.972
[sighs]

35:49.016 --> 35:50.148
[banging continues]

35:55.675 --> 35:56.589
[sighs]

35:58.939 --> 36:00.332
[banging continues]

36:01.376 --> 36:02.899
-[clamoring continues]
-Okay.

36:03.944 --> 36:05.772
Fine. You win.

36:07.077 --> 36:08.557
You want to know where I stand?

36:08.601 --> 36:09.993
All right.

36:10.037 --> 36:11.734
I will give my first, last,

36:11.778 --> 36:15.651
and only press conference
on the subject of my parents

36:15.695 --> 36:18.437
tonight at
La Bonne Nuit speakeasy,

36:18.480 --> 36:20.047
after a special performance.

36:20.613 --> 36:22.484
["All That Jazz" playing]

